    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="762"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d762">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12011a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mediators</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 18, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellencies</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that the
                    Special Commissioners of the President of the United States near the Mediators
                    in the conferences to be held at Niagara Falls, Ontario, will be the Honorable
                    Joseph Rucker Lamar, an Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United
                    States, and Mr. Frederick William <pb facs="0617" n="501" xml:id="pg_501"/>
                    Lehmann, formerly Solicitor General of the United States, who will be
                    accompanied by their secretary, H. Percival Dodge, Esquire.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Jennings Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
